# Access Ubuntu Server Remotely Using SSH and PuTTY

## Project Overview

This repository demonstrates how to remotely access an Ubuntu Server using the SSH protocol with the PuTTY client. Remote server access allows administrators and cybersecurity students to manage systems securely over a network.

This project explains the process of installing and configuring SSH on Ubuntu and connecting to the server remotely from a Windows system using PuTTY.

---

## Technologies Used

- Ubuntu Server
- SSH (Secure Shell)
- OpenSSH Server
- PuTTY SSH Client
- VirtualBox (for virtual environment)

